## 2. Data Warehousing

We established the following BigQuery infrastructure:

### Schema: `commercial_data.backerkit_projects`
| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `project_id` | STRING | Unique slug |
| [title](file:///C:/Users/Yorri/.gemini/latest_script.py#186-188) | STRING | Project Title |
| `funding_usd` | FLOAT | Current funding |
| `backers_count` | INTEGER | Total backers |
| `system_tag` | STRING | 5e/OSR/etc |

### Analysis: `commercial_data.backerkit_hype_analysis`
A derived table calculating the **Hype Signal** (Funding per Backer).
> [!WARNING]
> The planned join with `concept_library.dnd_keywords` was omitted because the dataset `concept_library` was missing from the environment. The table currently contains raw funding metrics.

